On-screen debug overlay + isolate data handlers + raise stand canopy/shop signs

The balance bar now renders but reads 0, and billboards show default text, so the
client is receiving empty/zero profile data. Since the Output window is hard to
reach, surface the truth ON SCREEN:

- ClientMain: a green DEBUG box shows profile-update count, the coins/stands the
  client actually received, and the last server message. One screenshot now tells
  us whether it's a no-data, zero-data, or UI-update problem. Also isolated the
  UIController vs StadiumController profile handlers in separate pcalls so one
  failing can't block the other (and the balance/billboards both update).
- PlotService: stand canopy floats higher (real overhead clearance, not a lid);
  storefront signs moved to the top of the shop face so the awning can't hide them.

